== JQuery JSlideshow ==

It's a plugin for create awesome slideshow, you can use it for any html tag.

=== Implementation ===

Include JSlideshow files to your html index file.

<script src="jslideshow.js" type="text/javascript">
<link href="jslideshow.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">

All you need is just a div tag with the class "slideshow".

<div class="slideshow">
</div>
<div id="slideshow-helper"></div>

Inside a .slideshow add a div with the class "slides".

<div class="slideshow">
  <div class="slides">
  </div>
</div>
<div id="slideshow-helper"></div>

And inside .slides you can append any html tag with the class "slide".

<div class="slideshow">
  <div class="slides">
    <div class="slide">
      <img src="" alt="">
    </div>
    <div class="slide">
      <img src="" alt="">
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div id="slideshow-helper"></div>

On your javascript file you need initialize the slideshow, all you have to do is just write this code:

$('.slideshow').slideshow();

That's it!

